form.current-chamber: IN THE SENATE OF THE UNITED STATES

action.action-desc: Mr. Menendez (for himself and Mr. Corker) (by request) introduced the following joint resolution; which was read twice and referred to the Committee on Foreign Relations

form.official-title: Relating to the approval of the proposed Third Amendment to the Agreement for Co-operation Between the United States of America and the International Atomic Energy Agency.

section.text: That the Congress does favor the proposed agreement for cooperation transmitted to the Congress by the President on January 29, 2014.
